==English==

===Etymology===
{{defdate|circa 1540}} From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{m|fr|réalité||quality of being real}}, {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|realité||property, possession}}, from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{m|la|realitas}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|realis||real}}. Recorded since 1550 as a legal term in the sense of “fixed property” (compare {{m|en|real estate}}, [[realty]]); the sense “real existence” is attested from 1647.

